11
0:00:41.417,000 --> 0:00:45,000
My outside self finally matched my inner truth,

12
0:00:45.547,000 --> 0:00:47,000
my inner self.

13
0:00:47.925,000 --> 0:00:51,000
For complicated reasons which I'll get to later,

14
0:00:52.082,000 --> 0:00:54,000
when I look at this picture,

15
0:00:55.03,000 --> 0:00:57,000
at that time I felt like, Geena, you've done it,

16
0:00:57.574,000 --> 0:00:58,000
you've made it,

17
0:00:58.913,000 --> 0:01:,000
you have arrived.

18
0:01:01.734,000 --> 0:01:03,000
But this past October,

19
0:01:04.324,000 --> 0:01:08,000
I realized that I'm only just beginning.

20
0:01:08.982,000 --> 0:01:12,000
All of us are put in boxes by our family,

21
0:01:13.112,000 --> 0:01:14,000
by our religion,

22
0:01:14.782,000 --> 0:01:15,000
by our society,

23
0:01:16.726,000 --> 0:01:18,000
our moment in history,

24
0:01:19.099,000 --> 0:01:21,000
even our own bodies.

25
0:01:21.571,000 --> 0:01:23,000
Some people have the courage to break free,

26
0:01:24.347,000 --> 0:01:26,000
not to accept the limitations imposed by

27
0:01:26.786,000 --> 0:01:27,000
the color of their skin

28
0:01:28.506,000 --> 0:01:31,000
or by the beliefs of those that surround them.

29
0:01:32.293,000 --> 0:01:33,000
Those people are always the threat

30
0:01:34.085,000 --> 0:01:35,000
to the status quo,

31
0:01:35.309,000 --> 0:01:39,000
to what is considered acceptable.

32
0:01:39.804,000 --> 0:01:44,000
In my case, for the last nine years,

33
0:01:45.593,000 --> 0:01:46,000
some of my neighbors,

34
0:01:47.287,000 --> 0:01:5,000
some of my friends, colleagues, even my agent,

35
0:01:50.291,000 --> 0:01:52,000
did not know about my history.

36
0:01:52.901,000 --> 0:01:55,000
I think, in mystery, this is called the reveal.

37
0:01:56.657,000 --> 0:01:59,000
Here is mine.

38
0:02:00.282,000 --> 0:02:02,000
I was assigned boy at birth

39
0:02:03.095,000 --> 0:02:06,000
based on the appearance of my genitalia.

40
0:02:06.177,000 --> 0:02:07,000
I remember when I was five years old

41
0:02:08.095,000 --> 0:02:1,000
in the Philippines walking around our house,

42
0:02:10.575,000 --> 0:02:13,000
I would always wear this t-shirt on my head.

43
0:02:13.946,000 --> 0:02:14,000
And my mom asked me,

44
0:02:15.441,000 --> 0:02:17,000
"How come you always wear that t-shirt on your head?"

45
0:02:18.021,000 --> 0:02:23,000
I said, "Mom, this is my hair. I'm a girl."

46
0:02:23.219,000 --> 0:02:27,000
I knew then how to self-identify.

47
0:02:27.656,000 --> 0:02:31,000
Gender has always been considered a fact,

48
0:02:32.363,000 --> 0:02:33,000
immutable,

49
0:02:34.235,000 --> 0:02:37,000
but we now know it's actually more fluid,

50
0:02:37.862,000 --> 0:02:41,000
complex and mysterious.

51
0:02:41.877,000 --> 0:02:43,000
Because of my success, I never had the courage

52
0:02:44.29,000 --> 0:02:46,000
to share my story,

53
0:02:46.94,000 --> 0:02:48,000
not because I thought what I am is wrong,

54
0:02:49.553,000 --> 0:02:52,000
but because of how the world treats those of us

55
0:02:52.555,000 --> 0:02:55,000
who wish to break free.

56
0:02:55.757,000 --> 0:02:56,000
Every day,

57
0:02:57.495,000 --> 0:03:,000
I am so grateful because I am a woman.

58
0:03:01.431,000 --> 0:03:04,000
I have a mom and dad and family

59
0:03:04.907,000 --> 0:03:06,000
who accepted me for who I am.

60
0:03:07.752,000 --> 0:03:11,000
Many are not so fortunate.

61
0:03:12.631,000 --> 0:03:14,000
There's a long tradition in Asian culture

62
0:03:14.706,000 --> 0:03:17,000
that celebrates the fluid mystery of gender.

63
0:03:18.284,000 --> 0:03:2,000
There is a Buddhist goddess of compassion.

64
0:03:21.085,000 --> 0:03:25,000
There is a Hindu goddess, hijra goddess.

65
0:03:25.351,000 --> 0:03:27,000
So when I was eight years old,

66
0:03:27.7,000 --> 0:03:29,000
I was at a fiesta in the Philippines celebrating

67
0:03:30.31,000 --> 0:03:32,000
these mysteries.

68
0:03:32.428,000 --> 0:03:34,000
I was in front of the stage,

69
0:03:34.866,000 --> 0:03:37,000
and I remember, out comes this beautiful woman

70
0:03:37.977,000 --> 0:03:38,000
right in front of me,

71
0:03:39.137,000 --> 0:03:41,000
and I remember that moment something hit me:

72
0:03:41.423,000 --> 0:03:44,000
That is the kind of woman I would like to be.

73
0:03:45.133,000 --> 0:03:47,000
So when I was 15 years old,

74
0:03:47.693,000 --> 0:03:48,000
still dressing as a boy,

75
0:03:49.11,000 --> 0:03:51,000
I met this woman named T.L.

76
0:03:51.524,000 --> 0:03:54,000
She is a transgender beauty pageant manager.

77
0:03:55.188,000 --> 0:03:56,000
That night she asked me,

78
0:03:56.87,000 --> 0:03:58,000
"How come you are not joining the beauty pageant?"

79
0:03:59.636,000 --> 0:04:01,000
