80
0:04:01.852,000 --> 0:04:04,000
that she would take care of the registration fee

81
0:04:05.175,000 --> 0:04:06,000
and the garments,

82
0:04:06.787,000 --> 0:04:08,000
and that night,

83
0:04:08.946,000 --> 0:04:1,000
I won best in swimsuit

84
0:04:11.026,000 --> 0:04:12,000
and best in long gown

85
0:04:12.54,000 --> 0:04:13,000
and placed second runner up

86
0:04:14.189,000 --> 0:04:17,000
among 40-plus candidates.

87
0:04:17.928,000 --> 0:04:19,000
That moment changed my life.

88
0:04:20.554,000 --> 0:04:21,000
All of a sudden, I was introduced

89
0:04:22.197,000 --> 0:04:24,000
to the world of beauty pageants.

90
0:04:25.066,000 --> 0:04:27,000
Not a lot of people could say that your first job

91
0:04:27.89,000 --> 0:04:28,000
is a pageant queen for transgender women,

92
0:04:29.702,000 --> 0:04:31,000
but I'll take it.

93
0:04:32.578,000 --> 0:04:34,000
So from 15 to 17 years old, I joined

94
0:04:34.871,000 --> 0:04:36,000
the most prestigious pageant

95
0:04:37.338,000 --> 0:04:41,000
to the pageant where it's at the back of the truck, literally,

96
0:04:41.879,000 --> 0:04:44,000
or sometimes it would be a pavement next to a rice field,

97
0:04:45.046,000 --> 0:04:46,000
and when it rains --

98
0:04:46.967,000 --> 0:04:48,000
it rains a lot in the Philippines --

99
0:04:49.714,000 --> 0:04:5,000
the organizers would have to move it

100
0:04:51.022,000 --> 0:04:55,000
inside someone's house.

101
0:04:55.097,000 --> 0:04:57,000
I also experienced the goodness of strangers,

102
0:04:57.374,000 --> 0:04:58,000
especially when we would travel

103
0:04:58.719,000 --> 0:05:,000
in remote provinces in the Philippines.

104
0:05:01.688,000 --> 0:05:02,000
But most importantly, I met

105
0:05:03.179,000 --> 0:05:06,000
some of my best friends in that community.

106
0:05:06.571,000 --> 0:05:08,000
In 2001,

107
0:05:08.997,000 --> 0:05:1,000
my mom, who had moved to San Francisco,

108
0:05:11.024,000 --> 0:05:14,000
called me and told me that my green card petition came through,

109
0:05:14.851,000 --> 0:05:17,000
that I could now move to the United States.

110
0:05:18.134,000 --> 0:05:19,000
I resisted it.

111
0:05:19.528,000 --> 0:05:21,000
I told my mom, "Mom, I'm having fun.

112
0:05:21.597,000 --> 0:05:21,000
I'm here with my friends,

113
0:05:22.507,000 --> 0:05:25,000
